$ indicates that none is variable on $\\approx1$-day\ntimescales, although flux variations of up to $\\sim25$\\% are observed on\n$\\approx100$-day timescales, typical of RQQs at similar redshifts. Significant\noptical-X-ray spectral slope variations observed in two of these sources are\nconsistent with the levels observed in luminous RQQs and are dominated by X-ray\nvariations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Sep 2017 18:03:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-18"}
